[[sn:Kaijin Shrine (Kinokawa)]] [[ja:%E6%B5%B7%E7%A5%9E%E7%A4%BE (%E7%B4%80%E3%81%AE%E5%B7%9D%E5%B8%82)]] [[ja:海神社]]

{{infobox religious building |religious_affiliation = {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto|qq=}} |image = {{religious_affiliation = {{ill|Shinto|ja|神道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto|qq=}}|image=Image Needed|cat=Kinokawa City}} |name = Kaijin Shrine (Kinokawa) |native_name = 海神社 |a11ress = {{ill|Wakayama Prefecture|ja|和歌山県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakayama Prefecture|qq=}}{{ill|Kinokawa City|ja|紀の川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinokawa City|qq=}}神領272 |location = |deity = {{ill|Watatsumi|ja|ワタツミ|lt=Toyotama-hiko no Mikoto|lt_ja=豊玉彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Watatsumi|qq=}}、国津姫命 |神体 = |社格 = Former {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|qq=}} |創建 = In the era of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Suinin|qq=}} |本殿 = |別名 = Kaijin-san |札所等 = |festival = October 15 (Third Sunday of October) |神事 = |location map = }}
'''Kaijin Shrine''' (海神社) is a {{ill|Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shrine|qq=}} located in the sacred territory of {{ill|Wakayama Prefecture|ja|和歌山県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Wakayama Prefecture|qq=}}{{ill|Kinokawa City|ja|紀の川市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kinokawa City|qq=}}. Its former Rank was {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|qq=}}. It is colloquially known as “Kaijin-san”.
== Deity == * Primary Deity – {{ill|Watatsumi|ja|ワタツミ|lt=Toyotama-hiko no Mikoto|lt_ja=豊玉彦命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Watatsumi|qq=}}, 国津姫命 * Auxiliary Deities – 穂高見命, {{ill|Toyotamahime Shrine|ja|トヨタマヒメ|lt=Toyotama-hime Shrine|lt_ja=豊玉姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyotamahime Shrine|qq=}}, {{ill|Tamayoribime Shrine|ja|タマヨリビメ|lt=Tamayoribime Shrine|lt_ja=玉依姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamayoribime Shrine|qq=}}, {{ill|Kotoshiranushi|ja|事代主|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshiranushi|qq=}}命
== History == Although the exact date of its foundation is unknown, the shrine is said to have been established in the era of {{ill|Emperor Suinin|ja|垂仁天皇|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Emperor Suinin|qq=}} when {{ill|Imibe no Sukune|ja|忌部宿禰|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imibe no Sukune|qq=}} received a divine revelation from the deity (the revered spirit that is said to have appeared at {{ill|Tategasaka|ja|楯ヶ崎|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tategasaka|qq=}} in {{ill|Kumano|ja|熊野|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kumano|qq=}})<ref name="紀の川市 海神社">[https://www.city.kinokawa.lg.jp/kanko/temples_shrines/kaijinja.html Kinokawa City Official Website – Kaijin Shrine]</ref> which led to its establishment<ref name="海神社">[https://wakayama-jinjacho.or.jp/jdb/sys/user/GetWjtTbl.php?JinjyaNo=3022 Wakayama Prefecture Shrine Office – Kaijin Shrine]</ref>.
Since ancient times, the Imperial Court’s veneration was profound, and it appears to have possessed many sacred estates. The area in which the shrine is enshrined is called “Shinryō”, and as its name indicates, it was the shrine’s own territory<ref name="海神社"/>.
In the {{ill|Tenshō|ja|天正|1=Tenshō (Momoyama period)|lt=Tenshō Era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenshō (Momoyama period)|qq=}} 13th year (1585), during the {{ill|Kishu Conquest|ja|紀州征伐|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kishu Conquest|qq=}} conducted by {{ill|Toyotomi Hideyoshi|ja|豊臣秀吉|lt=Hashiba Hideyoshi|lt_ja=羽柴秀吉|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyotomi Hideyoshi|qq=}}, the main hall and two subsidiary shrines, the worship hall, the Kagura hall, the treasure repository, and other structures were completely destroyed by military fire, with treasures and ancient records also burned<ref name="海神社"/>.
In April [[1873]] (the 6th year of {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}}), it was designated as a {{ill|Village Shrine|ja|郷社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Village Shrine|qq=}}. In September [[1942]] (the 17th year of {{ill|Showa|ja|昭和|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Showa|qq=}}), it was promoted to a {{ill|Prefectural Shrine|ja|県社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Prefectural Shrine|qq=}}<ref name="海神社"/>.
To the north of the shrine is {{ill|Kaijin Pond|ja|海神池|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaijin Pond|qq=}}.
== Shrine Grounds == * Main Hall<ref name="海神社"/> * Long Platform – Ritual Hall * Worship Hall (Wari-haiden) * Sacred Food Preparation Area * Shrine Implements Repository * Shrine Office * Mikoshi Storehouse
=== Subordinate Shrines === * Eastern Subordinate Shrine – 穂高見命社, {{ill|Tamayoribime Shrine|ja|タマヨリビメ|lt=Tamayoribime Shrine|lt_ja=玉依姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamayoribime Shrine|qq=}}社, {{ill|Toyotamahime Shrine|ja|トヨタマヒメ|lt=Toyotama-hime Shrine|lt_ja=豊玉姫命|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyotamahime Shrine|qq=}}社<ref name="kaijinnjya">[https://jun-yu-roku.com/kii-naga-jinryo-kai/ Shrine Tour – Kaijin Shrine]</ref> * Western Subordinate Shrine – 幸神社, {{ill|Inari Shrine|ja|稲荷社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Inari Shrine|qq=}}, {{ill|Kotoshiranushi|ja|事代主|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kotoshiranushi|qq=}}命 * {{ill|Kōtaigu Shrine|ja|皇大神宮|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kōtaigu Shrine|qq=}} – Deities: {{ill|Amaterasu|ja|天照大神|1=Amaterasu|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|lt=Amaterasu Ōmikami|lt_ja=天照皇大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu|13=User:Immanuelle/Amaterasu|qq=}}, {{ill|Toyouke|ja|トヨウケビメ|lt=Toyouke Ōmikami|lt_ja=豊受大神|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyouke|qq=}} * {{ill|Gion Shrine|ja|祇園社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gion Shrine|qq=}}
